###########################################################################
#  graph_default_color - a minimal @Graph that uses default (black)        #
#  axis lines, tick labels and plot strokes.  Exercises z53.c's "fold     #
#  default black to currentColor" rule on the raw-PostScript path that    #
#  @Graph rides through: every uncoloured stroke/fill emitted by the      #
#  graph package should reach the SVG output as currentColor rather than #
#  rgb(0,0,0).  rsvg-convert resolves currentColor to black when no CSS   #
#  cascade is set, so the raster output must still match the PS          #
#  reference pixel-for-pixel.                                             #
###########################################################################

@SysInclude { graph }
@SysInclude { doc }
@Doc @Text @Begin
@PP
A simple line graph with default-coloured axes and strokes:
@DP
@CentredDisplay -2p @Font @Graph
   style { axes }
   xorigin { 0 }
   yorigin { 0 }
   width { 7c }
   height { 4c }
   xticks { 0@ 1@ 2@ 3@ 4@ 5@ }
   yticks { 0@ 5@ 10@ 15@ 20@ 25@ }
   belowcaption { x }
   leftcaption { y }
{
   @Data pairs { solid }
   {
      0   0
      1   1
      2   4
      3   9
      4   16
      5   25
   }
}
@End @Text
